cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of estimating 3D trajectories from 2D projections, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves a deep learning model (cs.LG) that uses a novel tensor factorization technique (cs.AI) to improve the performance of fourth-order Boltzmann machines. The problem of trajectory estimation also has applications in robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE).
